Chelsea manager Graham Potter’s squad for his side’s Premier League tie with Fulham on Friday night has been revealed. According to Football London, Potter has released 25 players to tackle Fulham at Stamford Bridge today. Chelsea head to the game after playing a 0-0 draw with Liverpool in their last Premier League match. Here is Chelsea’s full squad against Fulham: Goalkeepers: Kepa Arrizabalaga, Edouard Mendy, Marcus Bettinelli, Gabriel Slonina Defenders: Trevoh Chalobah, Reece James, Thiago Silva, Benoit Badiashile, Cesar Azpilicueta, Marc Cucurella, Kalidou Koulibaly, Lewis Hall, Ben Chilwell Midfielders: Mason Mount, Conor Gallagher, Ruben Loftus-Cheek, Enzo Fernandez, Carney Chukwuemeka Attackers: Kai Havertz, Hakim Ziyech, Noni Madueke, Mykhailo Mudryk, Pierre-Emerick Aubameyang, David Datro Fofana, Omari Hutchinson. The kick-off time for the match is 9 pm.